---
import DocLayout from '../layouts/DocLayout.astro';
import PersonaCard from '../components/PersonaCard.astro';
import ResourceCard from '../components/ResourceCard.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---
<DocLayout
  title="Your team writes code with AI. Your review process doesn't know that."
  subtitle="VISDOM Code Review is a reference process for enterprise code review in the age of AI-assisted development. Not a tool — a process."
  tags={[
    { label: "VISDOM", variant: "green" },
    { label: "Reference Process", variant: "outline" },
  ]}
>

<p>
  Your developers use Copilot, Claude, Cursor. Your CI says the code is fine. Your tests pass.
  But 45% of AI-generated code contains OWASP vulnerabilities that those tests will never catch — because
  <strong>the AI wrote the tests too</strong>.
</p>

<p>
  Meanwhile, your senior engineers spend half their day reviewing code from distributed teams across
  time zones. PRs wait 24-48 hours. Standards drift between offices. Nobody trusts the AI output enough
  to ship it fast, but everybody's using it anyway.
</p>

<p>
  VISDOM Code Review (VCR) is how we solve this at VirtusLab — and how we help our clients solve it.
  It's a <strong>structured, multi-layered review process</strong> that we deploy on your teams, configure for
  your stack, and hand over for you to own.
</p>

<h2>Pick your path</h2>

<div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
  <a href={`${base}guide/leaders/`} class="block border-2 border-visdom-gray-200 hover:border-visdom-green rounded-lg p-5 no-underline transition-colors group">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
      <span class="text-2xl">📊</span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-700">For Leaders</span>
    </div>
    <h3 class="!mt-0 !text-base group-hover:text-visdom-green-dark">Engineering Managers, VPs, CTOs</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-visdom-gray-500 !mb-0">Business case, ROI model, what changes for your org, how we engage.</p>
  </a>

  <a href={`${base}guide/platform-engineers/`} class="block border-2 border-visdom-gray-200 hover:border-visdom-green rounded-lg p-5 no-underline transition-colors group">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
      <span class="text-2xl">🔧</span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-purple-100 text-purple-700">For Engineers</span>
    </div>
    <h3 class="!mt-0 !text-base group-hover:text-visdom-green-dark">Platform & DevOps Engineers</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-visdom-gray-500 !mb-0">Architecture, how to run a pilot, configuration, metrics setup.</p>
  </a>

  <a href={`${base}guide/developers/`} class="block border-2 border-visdom-gray-200 hover:border-visdom-green rounded-lg p-5 no-underline transition-colors group">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
      <span class="text-2xl">💻</span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-blue-100 text-blue-700">For Developers</span>
    </div>
    <h3 class="!mt-0 !text-base group-hover:text-visdom-green-dark">Developers on the team</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-visdom-gray-500 !mb-0">What changes in your daily PR workflow, how to read and give feedback.</p>
  </a>
</div>

<h2>The short version</h2>

<p>Every PR passes through layers of increasing depth — fast and cheap for trivial changes, thorough for risky ones:</p>

<div class="bg-visdom-gray-50 border border-visdom-gray-200 rounded-lg p-5 mb-6 font-mono text-sm">
<pre class="!bg-transparent !p-0 !mb-0 text-visdom-gray-600"><code>PR opened
  │
  ▼
Layer 0  Context Collection          &lt;10s    deterministic
Layer 1  Deterministic Gate          &lt;60s    linters, SAST, secrets
Layer 2  AI Quick Scan               &lt;2min   risk classification
Layer 3  AI Deep Review              &lt;10min  only MEDIUM+ risk
  │
  ▼
Structured PR comment + reviewer guidance</code></pre>
</div>

<p>
  A LOW-risk PR gets feedback in under 2 minutes at ~$0.05.
  A CRITICAL PR gets deep analysis across security, performance, architecture, and AI-code patterns — and
  your senior reviewer gets a pre-annotated PR that tells them exactly where to look.
</p>

<h2>What this is not</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Not a SaaS product</strong> — it's a reference process we implement on your infrastructure during a consulting engagement</li>
  <li><strong>Not tied to specific tools</strong> — the process works with any LLM provider, any CI platform, any code host. We provide reference implementations, you can swap components</li>
  <li><strong>Not a replacement for human review</strong> — it's a force multiplier. Seniors review fewer PRs, but with better context and focus</li>
</ul>

<h2>What your team is saying right now</h2>

<PersonaCard name="Your Engineering Manager" role="Katja's problem" color="green">
  <p>"My seniors in Kraków spend half their day reviewing PRs from the India team. The quality is inconsistent, feedback takes 24 hours, and we're shipping AI-generated code without really understanding what it does."</p>
</PersonaCard>

<PersonaCard name="Your Platform Engineer" role="Ewa's problem" color="purple">
  <p>"Our agents burn $30 per task because they loop on flaky tests. The CI lies to them. And nobody's tracking the real cost — leadership thinks AI costs us $950/month in Copilot licenses."</p>
</PersonaCard>

<PersonaCard name="Your Senior Developer" role="Rajesh's problem" color="blue">
  <p>"Copilot-generated PRs look clean but they're over-engineered — unnecessary Factory patterns, hallucinated APIs, tests that mirror the implementation instead of verifying it. I catch this stuff, but I can't review everything."</p>
</PersonaCard>

<p>
  <a href={`${base}before-after/`}>See concrete before/after scenarios →</a>
</p>

<h2>How we work with you</h2>

<div class="space-y-4 mb-8">
  <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
    <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-visdom-green text-white flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold">1</span>
    <div>
      <h3 class="!mt-0 !mb-1">Assessment</h3>
      <p class="text-sm !mb-0">We analyze your current review process, CI pipeline, test reliability, and team structure. We identify where VCR layers address your specific gaps.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
    <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-visdom-green text-white flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold">2</span>
    <div>
      <h3 class="!mt-0 !mb-1">Pilot on 1-2 teams</h3>
      <p class="text-sm !mb-0">We deploy VCR on your infrastructure — configured for your stack, your conventions, your risk thresholds. Working pipeline, real PRs, real feedback.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
    <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-visdom-green text-white flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold">3</span>
    <div>
      <h3 class="!mt-0 !mb-1">Tune and measure</h3>
      <p class="text-sm !mb-0">We track ITS, CPI, TORS, and developer satisfaction. We tune prompts, risk thresholds, and lens configurations based on real data from your teams.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
    <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-visdom-green text-white flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold">4</span>
    <div>
      <h3 class="!mt-0 !mb-1">Handover</h3>
      <p class="text-sm !mb-0">Your team owns VCR. We transfer knowledge, documentation, and operational ownership. You roll out to more teams on your own timeline.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<h2>Part of VISDOM</h2>

<p>
  VCR sits within the <strong>Automated Risk Assessment</strong> pillar of
  <a href="https://virtuslab.com/services/visdom">VISDOM</a> — VirtusLab's Agent-Ready SDLC offering.
  Alongside Context Fabric and Machine-Speed CI, it forms the infrastructure that makes
  AI-assisted development reliable at enterprise scale.
</p>

<p>
  Read the thinking behind it: <a href="https://virtuslab.com/blog/ai/the-fallacy">The Agent-Ready SDLC series</a>
</p>

<h2>Go deeper</h2>

<div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-3 mb-8">
  <ResourceCard
    title="Before / After Scenarios"
    description="4 concrete scenarios showing what changes when VCR is deployed."
    href={`${base}before-after/`}
    tag="SCENARIOS"
    tagColor="blue"
  />
  <ResourceCard
    title="Technical Reference"
    description="Full architecture, layer docs, configuration, metrics framework."
    href={`${base}reference/`}
    tag="REFERENCE"
    tagColor="purple"
  />
  <ResourceCard
    title="Reference Implementations"
    description="Technology-agnostic table of components and alternatives."
    href={`${base}reference/reference-implementations/`}
    tag="REFERENCE"
    tagColor="green"
  />
</div>

</DocLayout>
